To deploy vLLM, you can use the following steps:

1. **Choose a deployment framework**: vLLM supports deployment on cloud GPUs using the [Modal](https://modal.com) serverless computing platform, or on NVIDIA GPUs using the [Triton Inference Server](https://github.com/triton-inference-server).

2. **Use Kubernetes**: Deploy vLLM with Kubernetes to efficiently scale and manage ML models leveraging GPU resources.

3. **Integrate with KubeAI**: If you're using KubeAI, you can deploy and manage AI models on Kubernetes.

4. **Use KubeRay**: For deploying models with Ray, you can integrate vLLM with KubeRay.

5. **Automate Parameter Tuning**: If you're using benchmarks, you can automate the process of finding the optimal server parameter combinations for maximum throughput.

The deployment process involves setting up the necessary infrastructure and configurations to run vLLM on your chosen platform.
